<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikumaks </eesti>
<inglise>Head tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikumaksu maksavad 18 - 65-aastased valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Head tax shall be paid by the residents of a rural municipality or city who are between 18 and 65 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikumaksu m&auml;&auml;ra v&otilde;i diferentseeritud m&auml;&auml;rad kehtestab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rate or differentiated rates of head tax are established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isikumaksuga maksustamise periood on kalendriaasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The taxable period for head tax is one calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isikumaksust on vabastatud tegevteenistuses olevad ajateenijad ning I ja II grupi invaliidid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Conscripts in active service and category I and II disabled persons are exempt from head tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud v&auml;hemalt &uuml;heks kuuks t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;etud maksumaksja taotluse alusel kinni pidama tema t&ouml;&ouml;tasust igakuiselt 1/12 isikumaksu aastasummast ja kandma selle &uuml;le maksumaksja poolt deklareeritud elukohaj&auml;rgse kohaliku omavalitsuse eelarvesse v&auml;ljamakse tegemisele j&auml;rgneva kuu 5. kuup&auml;evaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) On the basis of an application by a taxpayer who is hired for at least one month, an employer is required to withhold 1/12 of the annual amount of head tax from his or her remuneration each month and to transfer it to the budget of the local government of the residence declared by the taxpayer by the fifth day of the month following the making of a payment. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Isikud, kes ei ole vabastatud isikumaksust ning kellelt ei peeta seda maksu kinni k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 5. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud korras, deklareerivad volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud maksuhaldurile oma elukoha aadressi ja tasuvad isikumaksu v&auml;hemalt 1/4 suuruste osadena aastamaksu summast kvartalile j&auml;rgneva kuu 25. kuup&auml;evaks elukohaj&auml;rgse omavalitsuse eelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Persons who are not exempt from head tax and from whom such tax is not withheld pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection (5) of this section shall declare the address of their residence to the tax authority provided for in the regulation of the council and pay head tax to the budget of the local government of their residence in instalments of not less than one quarter of the annual amount of the tax by the twenty-fifth day of the month following the quarter. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Valla- ja linnavalitsusel on &otilde;igus anda isikumaksu soodustusi ja vabastusi volikogu poolt kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A rural municipality or city government has the right to provide head tax incentives and exemptions under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. (Kehtetu - 15.12.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. (Repealed -15.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>M&uuml;&uuml;gimaks </eesti>
<inglise>Sales tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&uuml;&uuml;gimaksu maksavad valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil kauplemis- v&otilde;i teenindusluba omavad f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjad ja juriidilised isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Sales tax shall be paid by sole proprietors and legal persons who hold trade or service licences within the territory of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.04.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.04.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&uuml;&uuml;gimaksuga maksustatakse maksumaksja poolt valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil m&uuml;&uuml;dud kaupade ja teenuste maksumus m&uuml;&uuml;gihinnas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Sales tax is imposed on the value of goods and services sold by the taxpayer within the territory of a city or rural municipality according to the selling price. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaupade ja teenuste m&uuml;&uuml;gihind k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on k&auml;ibemaksuseaduses (RT I 1993, 60, 847; 2000, 7, 41) defineeritud maksustatava k&auml;ibe maksustatav v&auml;&auml;rtus ilma m&uuml;&uuml;gimaksuta. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, the selling price of goods and services is the taxable value of taxable turnover, as defined in the Value Added Tax Act (RT I 1993, 60, 847; 2000, 7, 41), without sales tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.04.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.04.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) M&uuml;&uuml;gimaksu m&auml;&auml;ra kehtestab volikogu, kuid mitte rohkem kui 1% k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud kaupade ja teenuste maksumusest m&uuml;&uuml;gihinnas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rate of sales tax is established by the council but it shall not exceed 1 per cent of the value of the goods and services provided for in subsection (2) of this section according to the selling price. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) M&uuml;&uuml;gimaksuga maksustamise periood on kvartal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The taxable period for sales tax is one quarter. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maksumaksja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A taxpayer is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) arvestama valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil tema m&uuml;&uuml;dud kaupade ja teenuste maksumuselt m&uuml;&uuml;gimaksu volikogu maksum&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ra j&auml;rgi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) calculate sales tax according to the value of the goods and services sold by the taxpayer within the territory of a rural municipality or city pursuant to the rate provided for in the tax regulation issued by the council; </inglise>
<eesti>2) esitama volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud maksuhaldurile kvartalile j&auml;rgneva kuu 20. kuup&auml;evaks m&uuml;&uuml;gimaksu kohta rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud k&auml;ibedeklaratsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>2) submit a value added tax return concerning sales tax in the format established by the Minister of Finance to the tax authority provided for in the council regulation by the twentieth day of the month following the quarter; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tasuma m&uuml;&uuml;gimaksu kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvesse deklaratsiooni esitamise t&auml;htp&auml;evaks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) pay the sales tax into the budget of the local government within the term for submission of the tax return. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.04.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.04.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Valla- ja linnavalitsusel on &otilde;igus anda m&uuml;&uuml;gimaksu soodustusi ja vabastusi volikogu poolt kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A rural municipality or city government has the right to provide sales tax incentives and exemptions under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Paadimaks </eesti>
<inglise>Boat tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Paadimaksu maksavad tehnilisele &uuml;levaatusele kuuluvate kuni 12 meetri pikkuste paatide, jahtide ja kaatrite (edaspidi v&auml;ikelaevad) omanikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Boat tax shall be paid by owners of boats, yachts and launches (hereinafter small ships) which are up to twelve meters long and are subject to surveys. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Paadimaks tasutakse v&auml;ikelaeva asukohaj&auml;rgse omavalitsuse eelarvesse volikogu poolt kehtestatud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Boat tax shall be paid into the budget of the local government of the location of the boat during the term established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Paadimaksuga maksustamise periood on kalendriaasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The taxable period for boat tax is one calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui v&auml;ikelaev on registreeritud p&auml;rast maksustamisperioodi algust, maksustatakse see alates registreerimisele j&auml;rgnevast kuust proportsionaalselt maksustamisperioodi l&otilde;puni j&auml;&auml;nud kuude arvuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a small ship is registered after the beginning of the taxable period, tax is imposed on such small ship as of the month following registration in proportion to the number of months remaining until the end of the taxable period. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ikelaeva v&otilde;&otilde;randamise korral on paadimaksu tasunud isikul &otilde;igus taotleda makstud paadimaksu tagastamist kuude eest, mis on j&auml;&auml;nud v&auml;ikelaeva v&otilde;&otilde;randamise kuust maksustamisperioodi l&otilde;puni, maksukorralduse seaduse (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 1996, 35, 714; 49, 953; 78, 1379; 81, 1447; 1997, 24, 363; 29, 447; 48, 778; 51, 822; 73, 1201; 77, 1313; 1998, 40, 611; 86/87, 1409; 1999, 24, 360; 27, 394; 71, 685; 92, 823 ja 826) &sect; 10 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of the transfer of a small ship, the person who paid the boat tax has the right to apply for a refund of the boat tax paid for the months which remain from the month in which the small ship was transferred until the end of the taxable period, under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsections 10 (1) and (2) of the Taxation Act (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 1996, 35, 714; 49, 953; 78, 1379; 81, 1447; 1997, 24, 363; 29, 447; 48, 778; 51, 822; 73, 1201; 77, 1313; 1998, 40, 611; 86/87, 1409; 1999, 24, 360; 27, 394; 71, 685; 92, 823 and 826). </inglise>
<eesti>(05.04.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.04.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;ikelaevade registripidaja on kohustatud esitama valla- ja linnavalitsustele nende taotlusel igale kvartalile j&auml;rgneva kuu 15. kuup&auml;evaks nende territooriumil elunevatele ja asuvatele f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja juriidilistele isikutele kuuluvatena registreeritud ja registrist kustutatud v&auml;ikelaevade kohta paadimaksuga maksustamiseks vajalikud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) By the fifteenth day of the month following each quarter, the registrar of small ships is required to submit information necessary for the imposition of boat tax concerning small ships that are registered as belonging to natural persons who reside or legal persons whose seat is located within the territory of the rural municipality or city, and small ships that are deleted from the register, to the rural municipality or city government at the request thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Volikogul on &otilde;igus kehtestada v&auml;ikelaevadele diferentseeritud maksum&auml;&auml;rad ning keelata paadimaksu mittetasunud isikutele kuuluvate v&auml;ikelaevade tehniline &uuml;levaatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Councils have the right to establish differentiated tax rates for small ships and to prohibit the survey of small ships belonging to persons who have not paid boat tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Valla- ja linnavalitsusel on &otilde;igus anda paadimaksu soodustusi ja vabastusi volikogu poolt kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A rural municipality or city government has the right to provide boat tax incentives and exemptions under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Reklaami- ja kuulutusemaks </eesti>
<inglise>Advertisement tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reklaami- ja kuulutusemaksu maksavad f&uuml;&uuml;silised ja juriidilised isikud omavalitsuse territooriumil paigaldatud, samuti omavalitsuse territooriumil elunevatele ja asuvatele f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja juriidilistele isikutele kuuluvatena registreeritud &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukitele paigaldatud kuulutustelt ja reklaamilt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Advertisement tax shall be paid by natural and legal persons for notices and advertisements posted within the territory of the local government, and on public transport vehicles registered as belonging to natural persons who reside or legal persons whose seat is located within the territory of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksustamisele kuuluvate kuulutuste ja reklaami ning nende paigutuskohtade loetelu kehtestab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The list of notices and advertisements that are subject to taxation and places for posting thereof are established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reklaami- ja kuulutusemaksust on vabastatud riigi- ja omavalitsusasutuste kuulutused ning erakondade, valimisliitude ja &uuml;ksikkandidaatide valimiskampaania kuulutused ja reklaam. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Notices of state and local government agencies and notices and advertisements relating to the election campaigns of political parties, election coalitions and independent candidates are exempt from advertisement tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Reklaami- ja kuulutusemaksu m&auml;&auml;ra v&otilde;i diferentseeritud m&auml;&auml;rad kehtestab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rate or differentiated rates of advertisement tax are established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Reklaami- ja kuulutusemaks tasutakse omavalitsuse eelarvesse volikogu poolt kehtestatud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Advertisement tax shall be paid into the budget of the local government during the term established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Valla- ja linnavalitsusel on &otilde;igus anda reklaami- ja kuulutusemaksu soodustusi ja vabastusi volikogu poolt kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A rural municipality or city government has the right to provide advertisement tax incentives and exemptions under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Teede ja t&auml;navate sulgemise maks </eesti>
<inglise>Road and street closure tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teede ja t&auml;navate sulgemise maksu maksavad f&uuml;&uuml;silised ja juriidilised isikud demonstratsioonide, rongk&auml;ikude ja muude &uuml;rituste korraldamise, samuti ehitus- v&otilde;i remontt&ouml;&ouml;de puhul, kui sellega kaasneb &uuml;ldkasutatava tee, t&auml;nava, v&auml;ljaku, pargi, puhkeaala v&otilde;i selle osa sulgemine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Road and street closure tax shall be paid by natural and legal persons upon the organisation of demonstrations, parades and other events, and in the case of construction or maintenance works, if the closure of a public road, street, square, park, rest area or part thereof is involved. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teede ja t&auml;navate sulgemise maksu m&auml;&auml;ra v&otilde;i diferentseeritud m&auml;&auml;rad kehtestab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rate or differentiated rates of road and street closure tax are established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teede ja t&auml;navate sulgemise maks tasutakse omavalitsuse eelarvesse volikogu poolt kehtestatud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Road and street closure tax shall be paid into the budget of the local government during the term established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;idukimaks </eesti>
<inglise>Motor vehicle tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Mootors&otilde;idukimaksu maksavad riiklikus autoregistris registreeritud mootors&otilde;idukeid omavad v&otilde;i neid mootors&otilde;idukeid kasutavad maksu kehtestanud kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse territooriumil elavad f&uuml;&uuml;silised ja asuvad juriidilised isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Motor vehicle tax shall be paid by natural and legal persons who own motor vehicles registered in the national motor vehicle register, by natural persons who use such motor vehicles and who reside within the territory of the local government which imposes the tax, and legal persons which use such motor vehicles and whose seat is located within the territory of the local government which imposes the tax. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;iduki kasutaja on mootors&otilde;idukimaksu maksjaks, kui ta kasutab mootors&otilde;idukit rendilepingu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The user of a vehicle shall pay the motor vehicle tax if the motor vehicle is used on the basis of a commercial lease contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksum&auml;&auml;ra kehtestab volikogu diferentseerituna s&otilde;iduki registrimassi, lubatud teljekoormuse v&otilde;i mootori v&otilde;imsuse j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>The tax rate shall be imposed by the council as a differentiated rate according to the maximum authorised weight of the vehicle, the maximum authorised axle load or the engine power. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mootors&otilde;idukimaksuga ei maksustata: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Motor vehicle tax is not imposed on: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigi- ja omavalitsusasutuste, kaitsev&auml;e ja Kaitseliidu mootors&otilde;idukeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the motor vehicles of state and local government agencies, the armed forces and the National Defence League; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Eestisse akrediteeritud diplomaadi staatust omavate isikute, v&auml;lisriigi diplomaatiliste ja konsulaaresinduste, rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonide ning valitsustevaheliste koost&ouml;&ouml;programmide esinduste poolt kasutatavaid mootors&otilde;idukeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) motor vehicles used by persons with diplomatic status accredited to Estonia, foreign diplomatic missions and consular posts, representations of international organisations and intergovernmental co-operation programmes; </inglise>
<eesti>3) I ja II grupi invaliidide mootors&otilde;idukeid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the motor vehicles of category I and II disabled persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mootors&otilde;idukimaksuga maksustamise periood on kalendriaasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The taxable period for motor vehicle tax is one calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>Jooksval kalendriaastal p&auml;rast 30. juunit registreeritud mootors&otilde;idukite eest tasutakse mootors&otilde;idukimaksu 50% aastamaksu m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>If a motor vehicle is registered after 30 June, 50 per cent of the annual rate of motor vehicle tax shall be paid on the motor vehicle for the calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>Mootors&otilde;iduki v&otilde;&otilde;randamise korral on mootors&otilde;idukimaksu tasunud isikul &otilde;igus taotleda makstud mootors&otilde;idukimaksu tagastamist kuude eest, mis on j&auml;&auml;nud mootors&otilde;iduki v&otilde;&otilde;randamise kuust maksustamisperioodi l&otilde;puni, maksukorralduse seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of the transfer of a motor vehicle, the person who paid the motor vehicle tax has the right to apply for a refund of the motor vehicle tax paid for the months which remain from the month in which the motor vehicle was transferred until the end of the taxable period, under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsections 10 (1) and (2) of the Taxation Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(05.04.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </eesti>
<inglise>(05.04.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 196) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Mootors&otilde;idukimaks tasutakse mootors&otilde;iduki omaniku v&otilde;i kasutaja elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgse omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvesse volikogu poolt kehtestatud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Motor vehicle tax shall be paid into the budget of the local government of the residence or seat of the owner or user of the motor vehicle during the term established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riikliku autoregistri pidaja on kohustatud esitama valla- ja linnavalitsustele nende taotlusel igale kvartalile j&auml;rgneva kuu 15. kuup&auml;evaks nende territooriumil elavatele f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja asuvatele juriidilistele isikutele kuuluvatena v&otilde;i nende kasutatavatena registreeritud ja registrist kustutatud mootors&otilde;idukite kohta mootors&otilde;idukimaksuga maksustamiseks vajalikud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) By the fifteenth day of the month following each quarter, the registrar of the national motor vehicle register is required to submit information necessary for the imposition of motor vehicle tax concerning motor vehicles that are registered as belonging to or being used by natural persons who reside or legal persons whose seat is located within the territory of the rural municipality or city, and motor vehicles that are deleted from the register, to the rural municipality or city government at the request thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(26.01.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 16, 269) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.01.99 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 16, 269) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Loomapidamismaks </eesti>
<inglise>Animal tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Loomapidamismaksu maksavad loomade, kelle pidamine valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil on maksustatud, omanikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Animal tax shall be paid by the owners of animals the keeping of which within the territory of a rural municipality or city is subject to taxation. </inglise>
<eesti>Nende loomade loetelu kehtestab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>The list of such animals is established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loomapidamismaksust on vabastatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following are exempt from animal tax: </inglise>
<eesti>1) politsei, kaitsev&auml;e, piirivalve, tolli, Kaitseliidu ning tulet&otilde;rje- ja p&auml;&auml;steformeeringute teenistusloomade pidamine, kui neid kasutatakse teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks, samuti pimedate inimeste juhtkoerte pidamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the keeping of service animals belonging to the police, the armed forces, the Border Guard, customs authorities, the National Defence League and fire fighting and rescue units if they are used for the performance of their functions, and the keeping of guide dogs by blind persons; </inglise>
<eesti>2) loomapidamine valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil kuni &uuml;he kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the keeping of animals within the territory of a rural municipality or city for up to one month. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Loomapidamismaksuga maksustamise periood on kalendriaasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The taxable period for animal tax is one calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Loomapidamismaksu m&auml;&auml;rad kehtestab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rates of animal tax are established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Loomapidamismaks tasutakse omavalitsuse eelarvesse volikogu poolt kehtestatud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Animal tax shall be paid into the budget of the local government by the term established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Valla- ja linnavalitsusel on &otilde;igus anda loomapidamismaksu soodustusi ja vabastusi volikogu poolt kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A rural municipality or city government has the right to provide animal tax incentives and exemptions under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;bustusmaks </eesti>
<inglise>Entertainment tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&otilde;bustusmaksu maksavad: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Entertainment tax shall be paid by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil tasuliste meelelahutus&uuml;rituste korraldajad; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the organisers of recreational events within the territory of the rural municipality or city to which persons are admitted for a fee; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil asuvate meelelahutusasutuste omanikud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the owners of recreational establishments located within the territory of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;bustusmaks kehtestatakse m&uuml;&uuml;dud p&auml;&auml;smetelt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Entertainment tax is imposed on sold tickets. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasulise meelelahutus&uuml;rituse p&auml;&auml;smed kuuluvad registreerimisele valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuses, mille territooriumil &uuml;ritus toimub. </eesti>
<inglise>Tickets for recreational events to which persons are admitted for a fee are subject to registration with the rural municipality or city government within the territory of which the event takes place. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;bustusmaks tasutakse omavalitsuse eelarvesse volikogu poolt kehtestatud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Entertainment tax shall be paid into the budget of the local government during the term established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla- ja linnavalitsusel on &otilde;igus anda l&otilde;bustusmaksu soodustusi ja vabastusi volikogu poolt kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A rural municipality or city government has the right to provide entertainment tax incentives and exemptions under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;pps&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Final Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruse rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for violation of regulation of council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kehtestatud t&auml;htajast hiljem omavalitsuse eelarvesse tasutud kohaliku maksu summalt ja maksumaksja poolt maksuhalduri kasuks enammakstud summalt arvutatakse intressi maksukorralduse seaduse paragrahvis 28 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Interest is calculated on amounts of local tax paid into the budget of a local government after expiry of the established term and on excess amounts paid by taxpayers for the benefit of the tax authorities pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 28 of the Taxation Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vastutus maksum&auml;&auml;ruse rikkumise eest s&auml;testatakse maksukorralduse seaduse alusel samas maksum&auml;&auml;ruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Liability for violation of a tax regulation is provided for in the tax regulation, pursuant to the Taxation Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&auml;iendavalt maksmisele kuuluvad summad laekuvad omavalitsuse eelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Additional amounts to be paid shall be paid into the budget of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel tasumisele kuuluvad v&otilde;i nendest v&auml;hemmakstud summad n&otilde;utakse sisse tagantj&auml;rele viimase kolme aasta eest maksustamisperioodi algusest arvates, mil maksmata j&auml;&auml;nud v&otilde;i v&auml;hemmakstud summa v&auml;lja selgitati. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Amounts to be paid pursuant to a regulation of a council or underpaid amounts thereof are collected retroactively for the three previous years calculated from the beginning of the taxable period when the unpaid or underpaid amount is ascertained. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Dispute resolution </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksumaksjal on &otilde;igus taotleda volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruses muudatuste tegemist v&otilde;i selle t&uuml;histamist kohaliku omavalitsuse korralduse seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A taxpayer has the right to request the amendment or repeal of a regulation of a council pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Local Government Organisation Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksumaksjal on &otilde;igus 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul maksuhalduri maksuteate v&otilde;i ettekirjutuse k&auml;ttesaamisest arvates esitada maksustamise kohta vastulause maksuhaldurile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A taxpayer has the right to file an objection concerning taxation with a tax authority within thirty calendar days after receipt of a tax notice or precept of the tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maksuhalduri otsusega mitten&otilde;ustumisel p&ouml;&ouml;rdub maksumaksja kaebusega kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a taxpayer does not agree with a decision of a tax authority, the taxpayer may file an appeal with a court. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksumaksjal on &otilde;igus esitada kaebus kohtusse ka enne vastulause esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A taxpayer also has the right to file an appeal with a court before filing an objection. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kaebuse esitamine ei v&otilde;ta maksumaksjalt maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise kohustust, kuid kuni otsuse tegemiseni maksumaksja kaebuse kohta ei ole maksuhalduril &otilde;igust maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmiseks maksukorralduse seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The filing of an appeal does not relieve a taxpayer of the obligation to comply with a precept of a tax authority, but the tax authority does not have the right to collect tax arrears pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Taxation Act until a court order has been made concerning the appeal of the taxpayer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudatused maksukorralduse seaduses </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of Taxation Act </inglise>
<eesti>Maksukorralduse seaduses (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 24, 394 ja 54, 904) tehakse j&auml;rgmised muudatused: </eesti>
<inglise>The Taxation Act (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 24, 394 and 54, 904) is amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) paragrahvis 3 asendatakse s&otilde;nad "seaduses s&auml;testatud ja volikogu" s&otilde;nadega "seaduse alusel valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu (edaspidi volikogu)"; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in &sect; 3, the words "provided by law and imposed by a council in its administrative territory" are substituted by the words "imposed by a rural municipality or city council (hereinafter council) in its administrative territory pursuant to law"; </inglise>
<eesti>2) paragrahvi 7 punktist 3 j&auml;etakse v&auml;lja s&otilde;nad "kohaliku maksu puhul piirm&auml;&auml;rad"; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in clause 7 3), the words "in the case of a local tax, maximum rates" are omitted; </inglise>
<eesti>3) paragrahvi 11 5. l&otilde;ike esimene s&otilde;na "Maksuhaldurite" asendatakse s&otilde;nadega "Riiklike maksude maksuhaldurite"; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in subsection 11 (5), the words "the tax authorities" are substituted by the words "the tax authorities for state taxes"; </inglise>
<eesti>4) paragrahvi 14 1. l&otilde;ige muudetakse ja s&otilde;nastatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>4) subsection 14 (1) is amended and worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"(1) Riiklike maksude maksuhaldurid on Maksuamet ja Tolliamet ning nende kohalikud talitused. </eesti>
<inglise>"(1) The tax authorities for state taxes are the Tax Board and the Customs Board and their local offices. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalike maksude maksuhaldurid oma haldusterritooriumil on valla- ja linnavalitsused ning vastavalt kohalike maksude seaduse paragrahv 3 3. l&otilde;ikele Maksuameti kohalikud talitused"; </eesti>
<inglise>The tax authorities for local taxes are the rural municipality and city governments within their administrative territories, and the Tax Board local offices pursuant to subsection 3 (3) of the Local Taxes Act. &ldquo;; </inglise>
<eesti>5) paragrahvi 30 2. l&otilde;iget t&auml;iendatakse lausega j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>5) subsection 30 (2) is amended by adding a sentence with the following wording: </inglise>
<eesti>"Kohalike maksude seaduse rikkumise asja arutamise ja karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on volikogu poolt volitatud ametiisikul." </eesti>
<inglise>"An official authorised by the council has the right to hear a matter concerning violation of the Local Taxes Act and to impose punishment." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku t&auml;iendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of Code of Administrative Offences </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; 1993, 7, 103; RT I 1993, 33, 539; 44, 637; 62, 891; 72/73, 1019; 1994, 1, 5; 12, 202; 23, 385; 24, 391; 28, 424 ja 427; 34, 532 ja 534; 39, 620; 46, 773; 48, 789 ja 50, 845) paragrahv 188 teksti t&auml;iendatakse p&auml;rast arvu "140" arvuga "141". </eesti>
<inglise>The Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; 1993, 7, 103; RT I 1993, 33, 539; 44, 637; 62, 891; 72/73, 1019; 1994, 1, 5; 12, 202; 23, 385; 24, 391; 28, 424 and 427; 34, 532 ja 534; 39, 620; 46, 773; 48, 789 ja 50, 845) is amended by adding the number "141" after the number "140" to the text of &sect; 188. </inglise>
